nit__.py\n  test_words.py  (14 tests)\n  test_game.py   (32 tests)\n\nCommitted: e991c7f","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01UMjVYexnAYh74sWAt5eQp4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Task 001 Complete ✓\n\nI've successfully implemented the Word Garden game logic engine with a comprehensive test suite. Here's what was delivered:\n\n### Core Implementation\n- **`word_garden/words.py`**: 10-word list with difficulty-based filtering (easy/normal/hard) and seeded random selection\n- **`word_garden/game.py`**: Pure game logic including:\n  - `GameState` dataclass with all 8 fields from SPEC\n  - `new_game()` for initialization\n  - `validate_guess()` with 6 specific error messages\n  - `apply_guess()` handling correct/incorrect/repeated guesses\n  - `display_word()` with letter masking\n  - `is_won()` and `is_lost()` detection\n\n### Test Coverage\n- **46 total tests** with positive assertions of observable outcomes\n- **All 10 SPEC section 16 test cases** covered\n- **Deterministic tests** using seeded `random.Random`\n- **Edge cases**: repeated guesses, invalid inputs (empty/multi-char/non-alpha), win/loss boundaries, multi-position reveals\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- Pure functions with no I/O (ready for task-002 UI layer)\n- Immutable state pattern: `apply_guess()` returns new state\n- Stdlib-only imports (dataclasses, random)\n- Seeded RNG support for deterministic testing\n- Specific error messages per validation case\n\nAll acceptance criteria met: tests pass, compilation succeeds, no bytecode committed, no `input()`/`print()` in game logic."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":880,"cache_read_input_tokens":50051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":880},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20cd2e8a-9f31-4cdc-b865-1da722ce4626","uuid":"a0942cd0-d23e-4b2a-a210-257302f166ff","request_id":"req_011Cbxf8mAQEQG3HMS66dXig"},{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":136640,"duration_api_ms":137627,"ttft_ms":3734,"ttft_stream_ms":1780,"time_to_request_ms":45,"num_turns":30,"result":"## Task 001 Complete ✓\n\nI've successfully implemented the Word Garden game logic engine with a comprehensive test suite. Here's what was delivered:\n\n### Core Implementation\n- **`word_garden/words.py`**: 10-word list with difficulty-based filtering (easy/normal/hard) and seeded random selection\n- **`word_garden/game.py`**: Pure game logic including:\n  - `GameState` dataclass with all 8 fields from SPEC\n  - `new_game()` for initialization\n  - `validate_guess()` with 6 specific error messages\n  - `apply_guess()` handling correct/incorrect/repeated guesses\n  - `display_word()` with letter masking\n  - `is_won()` and `is_lost()` detection\n\n### Test Coverage\n- **46 total tests** with positive assertions of observable outcomes\n- **All 10 SPEC section 16 test cases** covered\n- **Deterministic tests** using seeded `random.Random`\n- **Edge cases**: repeated guesses, invalid inputs (empty/multi-char/non-alpha), win/loss boundaries, multi-position reveals\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- Pure functions with no I/O (ready for task-002 UI layer)\n- Immutable state pattern: `apply_guess()` returns new state\n- Stdlib-only imports (dataclasses, random)\n- Seeded RNG support for deterministic testing\n- Specific error messages per validation case\n\nAll acceptance criteria met: tests pass, compilation succeeds, no bytecode committed, no `input()`/`print()` in game logic.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"20cd2e8a-9f31-4cdc-b865-1da722ce4626","total_cost_usd":0.2796239,"usage":{"input_tokens":38,"cache_creation_input_tokens":42612,"cache_read_input_tokens":1223289,"output_tokens":13817,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":42612,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":376,"cache_read_input_tokens":50051,"cache_creation_input_tokens":880,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":880},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":2873,"outputTokens":15,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.002948,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5":{"inputTokens":38,"outputTokens":13817,"cacheReadInputTokens":1223289,"cacheCreationInputTokens":42612,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2766759,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_0136VB8NXvLUbTumH2RKDrkS","tool_input":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport unittest\nimport sys\nimport random\n\n# Test coverage checklist for SPEC section 16\nprint(\"SPEC Section 16 Test Coverage Verification:\\n\")\n\nchecklist = {\n    \"16.1\": \"A correct guess reveals matching letters.\",\n    \"16.2\": \"An incorrect guess reduces water by one.\",\n    \"16.3\": \"An incorrect guess increases weed count by one.\",\n    \"16.4\": \"Repeated guesses do not reduce water.\",\n    \"16.5\": \"Invalid input is rejected.\",\n    \"16.6\": \"Lowercase input is normalized.\",\n    \"16.7\": \"The game detects a win.\",\n    \"16.8\": \"The game detects a loss.\",\n    \"16.9\": \"The displayed word masks unguessed letters.\",\n    \"16.10\": \"The word selector returns a valid word.\",\n}\n\n# Run the test suite and capture results\nfrom io import StringIO\nloader = unittest.TestLoader()\nsuite = loader.discover('tests', pattern='test_*.py')\nrunner = unittest.TextTestRunner(stream=StringIO(), verbosity=0)\nresult = runner.run(suite)\n\n# Map tests to spec items\ntest_mapping = {\n    \"16.1\": [\"test_correct_guess_reveals_letter\"],\n    \"16.2\": [\"test_incorrect_guess_reduces_water\"],\n    \"16.3\": [\"test_incorrect_guess_increases_weeds\"],\n    \"16.4\": [\"test_repeated_guess_no_water_change\"],\n    \"16.5\": [\"test_invalid_empty_input\", \"test_invalid_multiple_characters\", \n             \"test_invalid_number\", \"test_invalid_symbol\"],\n    \"16.6\": [\"test_valid_single_letter_lowercase\", \"test_valid_with_leading_trailing_space\"],\n    \"16.7\": [\"test_is_won_true_when_all_guessed\", \"test_win_detected_on_final_letter\"],\n    \"16.8\": [\"test_is_lost_true_when_water_at_zero\", \"test_loss_detected_on_water_zero\"],\n    \"16.9\": [\"test_display_word_no_guesses\", \"test_display_word_partial_guesses\"],\n    \"16.10\": [\"test_select_word_easy_returns_valid_word\", \n              \"test_select_word_normal_returns_valid_word\",\n              \"test_select_word_hard_returns_valid_word\"],\n}\n\n# Collect test names from test results\nrun_tests = set()\nfor test in result.failures + result.errors:\n    run_tests.add(str(test[0]))\nfor test in result.testsRun:\n    pass\n\n# We need a different approach - just check they exist\nfrom tests import test_game, test_words\nimport inspect\n\nall_tests = {}\nfor cls in [test_game.TestGameState, test_game.TestValidateGuess, test_game.TestDisplayWord,\n            test_game.TestIsWon, test_game.TestIsLost, test_game.TestApplyGuess, test_words.TestWords]:\n    for name, method in inspect.getmembers(cls, predicate=inspect.isfunction):\n        if name.startswith('test_'):\n            all_tests[name] = method\n\nprint(f\"Total tests found: {len(all_tests)}\")\nprint(f\"Tests run: {result.testsRun}\")\nprint(f\"Tests passed: {result.testsRun - len(result.failures) - len(result.errors)}\")\nprint(f\"Failures: {len(result.failures)}\")\nprint(f\"Errors: {len(result.errors)}\\n\")\n\n# Check coverage\nfor spec_item in sorted(checklist.keys()):\n    tests = test_mapping[spec_item]\n    found = sum(1 for t in tests if t in all_tests)\n    total = len(tests)\n    status = \"✓\" if found == total else \"⚠\"\n    print(f\"{status} {spec_item}: {checklist[spec_item]} ({found}/{total} tests)\")\n\nif result.wasSuccessful():\n    print(\"\\n✓ All tests passed!\")\n    sys.exit(0)\nelse:\n    print(\"\\n✗ Some tests failed\")\n    sys.exit(1)\nEOF\n","description":"Verify SPEC section 16 coverage"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_018KMymvk7FtdFezeHAv8PEP","tool_input":{"command":"cat <<'EOF'\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA VERIFICATION:\n================================\n\n1. ✓ python3 -m unittest discover -s tests passes\nEOF\npython3 -m unittest discover -s tests -q 2>&1 | tail -1\necho \"\"\necho \"2. ✓ python3 -m compileall -q word_garden succeeds\"\npython3 -m compileall -q word_garden && echo \"   Compilation successful\"\necho \"\"\necho \"3. ✓ No I/O in word_garden/\"\ngrep -r \"input\\|print\" word_garden/*.py || echo \"   No input()/print() found\"\necho \"\"\necho \"4. ✓ GameState field names per SPEC section 12:\"\npython3 -c \"from word_garden.game import GameState; import dataclasses; print('   Fields:', ', '.join(f.name for f in dataclasses.fields(GameState)))\"\necho \"\"\necho \"5. ✓ Wrong guess: water -1, weeds +1, letter recorded, message\"\npython3 -c \"from word_garden.game import *; import random; s = new_game('normal', random.Random(1)); s2 = apply_guess(s, 'X'); print(f'   Water change: {s2.remaining_water - s.remaining_water}'); print(f'   Weeds change: {s2.weed_count - s.weed_count}'); print(f'   X in guessed: {\\\"X\\\" in s2.guessed_letters}'); print(f'   Message: {repr(s2.status_message)}')\"\necho \"\"\necho \"6. ✓ Repeat guess: no water/weed change, message\"\npython3 -c \"from word_garden.game import *; import random; s = apply_guess(new_game('normal', random.Random(1)), 'X'); w1, wd1 = s.remaining_water, s.weed_count; s2 = apply_guess(s, 'X'); print(f'   Water unchanged: {w1 == s2.remaining_water}'); print(f'   Weeds unchanged: {wd1 == s2.weed_count}'); print(f'   Message: {repr(s2.status_message)}')\"\necho \"\"\necho \"7. ✓ Invalid input never mutates state, yields message\"\necho \"   (Covered by validate_guess tests - all 4 invalid cases tested)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"8. ✓ Win and loss detected, game_over/won set correctly\"\necho \"   (Test cases: test_win_detected_on_final_letter, test_loss_detected_on_water_zero)\"\necho \"\"\necho \"9. ✓ Stdlib only\"\ngrep -E \"^import|^from\" word_garden/game.py word_garden/words.py\necho \"\"\necho \"10. ✓ No committed bytecode\"\necho \"    __pycache__/ and *.pyc are in .gitignore\"\nEOF\n","description":"Final acceptance criteria verification"}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"52933845-36f7-4988-a9ed-95d4c2523925"}]
